        <updateDate>2025-08-04T19:35:17Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PFAS–Free Procurement Act of 2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill prohibits an executive agency from renewing or entering into a contract for the procurement of covered items that contain&amp;nbsp;perfluorooctane sulfonate (PFOS) or perfluorooctanoic acid (PFOA). Under the bill, &lt;em&gt;covered items &lt;/em&gt;means (1) nonstick cookware and cooking utensils; and (2) furniture, carpet, and any rug treated with stain-resistant coating.&amp;nbsp;Both PFOS and PFOA are types of&amp;nbsp;per- and&amp;nbsp;polyfluoroalkyl substances, commonly known as PFAS. PFAS are man-made and may have adverse human health effects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The bill also specifies that agencies must prioritize the procurement of covered items that do not contain&amp;nbsp;PFAS.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
